2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper investigates the effect of limited phase shifts on the performance of a communication system, which is a common problem in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the design and control of a reconfigurable intelligent surface, which is a typical problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper discusses the enhancement of communication quality, which is closely related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society): The paper may have implications for the societal impact of reconfigurable intelligent surfaces on communication systems.
